# Copy to `.env` for local builds and Wrangler deploy prep (see wrangler.toml).
#
# Required when large hero/group MP4s live on R2 (Cloudflare Pages 25 MiB/file limit).
# Without this at `astro build` time, `<source>` URLs stay `/assets/video/…` on your Pages
# origin and playback fails if those files were offloaded from the repo bundle.
#
# Public R2 URL or custom domain — no trailing slash.
# Object keys in the bucket must match site paths exactly, e.g. `assets/video/hero-bg-web.mp4`.
# Enable “Allow Access” / public bucket URL (`*.r2.dev`) or a custom domain on the bucket.
#
# Cloudflare Pages (Git deployments): Settings → Environment variables → add
# PUBLIC_TM_MEDIA_BASE for Production (and Preview if needed).
#
# In your real `.env`, the variable line must NOT start with `#` or the build ignores it.
#
# Use either:
#   PUBLIC_TM_MEDIA_BASE=https://pubxxxxxxxxxxxx.r2.dev
# or shell-style (now supported):
#   export PUBLIC_TM_MEDIA_BASE=https://pubxxxxxxxxxxxx.r2.dev
